.TH "sysfs_update_groups" 9 "sysfs_update_groups" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sysfs_update_groups \- given a directory kobject, create a bunch of attribute groups
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sysfs_update_groups
.BI "(struct kobject *kobj "  ","
.BI "const struct attribute_group **groups "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "kobj" 12
The kobject to update the group on
.IP "groups" 12
The attribute groups to update, NULL terminated
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function update a bunch of attribute groups.  If an error occurs when
updating a group, all previously updated groups will be removed together
with already existing (not updated) attributes.

Returns 0 on success or error code from sysfs_update_group on failure.
